
[1]shamefully

   SHA'MEFULLY, adv.

   1. Disgracefully; in a manner to bring reproach. He shamefully deserted
   his friend.

   2. With indignity or indecency; in a manner that may cause shame.

   How shamefully that maid he did torment. Spenser.
